        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Also off topic,</P><P>Having played UO for a while myself and only quitting because of the lag (and the huge delay in second teir of housing if you remember) I just thought i'd share a few thoughts I have about eq vs ultima. In ultima you could pretty much do what you wanted and make your own adventure. Sure the graphics arent as good and the lag was sometimes ubearable but you had freedom and you could be making money even as a beginner.  In eq , at least in my opinon, decent cash and items are hard to come buy as a newbie. Even 50+ you have to wait around for groups, rare drops, and then win the lottot over anyone else in your group. So what im trying to say is dont expect to start up eq and start making cash and finding good items. Far too much of eq is based on level and most of my friends and myself resolved to level asap and then try and make money. A little disappointing i would say, coming from uo, but otherwise i think you'll have a blast with eq. I just miss the days of coming home to a nice golden chest absolutely crammed with gold =)</P><P>just thought i'd speak my mind so you wouldnt be shocked the way i was =)</P><P> </font></td>
