        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Here's my rundown of it:</P><P>Gnome:<BR>--People that play gnomes play them because they are gnomes. You dont have as many faction issues as some of the other races and they are always amusing to watch.</P><P>Erudite:<BR>--Very high starting int. Distinguished look (sortta) The int bonus doesn't do much for you at higher levels since you will have TONS of gear to get your stats up there but it does allow for a better selection of resist and HP and Mana gear. I play an Erudite</P><P>Iksar:<BR>--Arguable the best min/max character there is. You int is lower but not cripling since as I said you can get tons of items to raise it. The regen for them is awsome, you can sit in Alure of Death and still gain HP meaning you always have it on. When you get CoB you can stay in that and only lose I think 1 or hp when you get higher level so again you're almost always using it and being in CoB all the time is as good as being in Lich part time really. Over all you become more efficient at what is our bigest soloing, downtime reducing tool. Very nice class and they look cool too.</P><P>Dark Elf:<BR>--Cookie cutter :) Sorry guys but I see way too many Dark Elves but thats just me. My character in Beta was a DE Necro and had I played at release my main would be as well. All around descent characters, Neriak rocks, faction isn't a big deal</P><P>Human:<BR>--Unique. Avarage stats. You dont see many human anything most of the time. </P><P>I think you might be happiest with Iksar. You might have to spend some time working on faction is some places to use the merchants so that you can get food and such when you hunt outside of Kunark but thats not much of an issue really.</P><P>Philiak Mortus Lv.49 Necromancer of Xev<BR>Slisik n00bie Shaman of Povar<BR>Sam: Where should I put this thing so that it doesnt hurt anyone we know or care about?<BR>Max: Out the window Sam. There's nobody but strangers out there.<BR><a href="http://www.pvponline.com" target="_blank">www.pvponline.com</a></P><P>Edited by - kinada on 05/08/2001  17:45:17</font></td>
