        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>I feel i have to mention one thing, you can't improve your forage skill as on iksar it starts at 50 and caps at 50 (i'm pretty sure on this, if i'm wrong please someone tell me).  So while you CAN forage for food/drink, it is rather annoying.  Personally i keep atleast a bag full of food/drink and when i can ask for some summoned so i don't waste my own.  Getting faction up to none-KOS isn't really hard, it is just time consuming.  I chose gfay area because i'm on povar and that is auction heaven...and with CB it is really easy, also it raises my faction with 3 cities (4? wood elves, dorfs, gnomes, and high elves?) which helps a lot too.  Freeport is another good area to get faction up, but it is a bit harder, no zone you can clear to get it...basically you can jsut take the little orc camps, or kill the guards :) that is right, killing the guards can get you partially unKOS in north (which is where the bank is...reason is that the paladins control the norht and they don't like the normal malitia)</P><P><marquee><b><font=red> ABILLISTER "MONKEY" ABU-Povar</font></b></marquee><BR><marquee><a href="<a href="http://whiteangels.guildsofeq.com/MainFrame.asp" target="_blank">http://whiteangels.guildsofeq.com/MainFrame.asp</a>" target="_New">Sojourn's Talon</a></marquee></font></td>
