        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Ssauron</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Either my forage skill is really low or I am just unlucky as all heck.  I still have to buy food and on occasion water.  I do not think that the Iksar forage skill is nearly as self sustainig as my cousin the wood elf's was.  He could feed whole armies with his foraging skills, mine I am lucky to keep myself fed.  Someone once told me that Iksar forage was capped at 50, the last time I saw a skill increase on the wood elf (at level 51) was skill of 186.  As far as I can remember I have never seen a Forage skill increase with my Iksar.</P><P>That aside playing a Iksar necro has been most entertaining and enjoyable.  You have a nice regen ability, plenty of hunting close to home and typically lots of Iksar bretheren to hang with.  I love the enviroments of the Iksar world and the underlying stories and feeling of the zones in the Kunark lands adds a lot of depth to Everquest in my opinion.  Personally I have only hunted off the island of Kunark on a handfull of occasions (ie sand giants and specs in oasis as revenge for all the awful times they killed my ranger cousin =p) and have no real reason for leaving anytime soon.  I have hunted in nearly every Kunark zone appropriate to my level along the way.  Some of the best loot/exp can be found just a short run from the gates of Cabilis.</P><P>Spend some time raising an Iksar up in their home lands and you will see what I mean.  I am not the type to create a character and then go run to where I leveled my Wood Elf (insert other class/race combo here) just because I was familar with it.  In fact I feel I should be hated by the other races when I visit their lands...  In time you can head to Velious and have faction just like everyone else, but untill then stay in Kunark (I like TD too...  for the occasional island vacation, but I still consider this Kunark...), level up, get some loot and enjoy the story behind the Iksar people and their ancient lands.</P><P>Ssauron<BR>~49th Iksar Necro<BR>~West Cabilis, Kunark<BR>~Rodcet Nife</font></td>
